      "titleArabic": "أنواع الجمل العربية",
      "content": [
        "Arabic has two main sentence types: nominal (jumla ismiyya) beginning with a noun, and verbal (jumla fi'liyya) beginning with a verb. Each has distinct grammatical rules."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Nominal sentences begin with mubtada' (subject)",
        "Verbal sentences begin with a verb",
        "Maṣdar mu'awwal (أن + verb) can act as a noun",
        "Complete and incomplete verbs have different behaviors"
      ],
      "examples": [
