    {
      "title": "Form X Verbs (اِسْتَفْعَلَ)",
      "titleArabic": "باب اِسْتَفْعَلَ",
      "content": [
        "Form X verbs are formed by prefixing اِسْتَ to the root. This pattern typically indicates seeking, asking for, or considering something to have a quality."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern: اِسْتَفْعَلَ (istaf'ala) - with prefix ista",
        "Maṣdar pattern: اِسْتِفْعَال (istif'āl)",
        "Indicates seeking: اِسْتَغْفَرَ (to seek forgiveness)",
        "Can mean considering: اِسْتَحْسَنَ (to consider good)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَغْفَرَ", "english": "to seek forgiveness" },
